		{ label: `Pew Research — The Future of World Religions (2010–2050 Projections)`, url: `https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2015/04/02/religious-projections-2010-2050/` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for those who seek peace`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The path you know teaches that suffering is real and that peace is worth seeking with your whole life — and that is true and good. The Father's Heart Bible™ offers something it does not ask you to first reject: it introduces a personal <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — not a force, not an idea, but One who knows you by name and meets you in your suffering.</p><p>Where the path can feel like a long road walked by your own effort, the Father offers to walk it with you. He does not ask you to strive your way into His favor before He will come near. He comes near first. He sees the suffering you have faced so honestly, and instead of asking you to climb to Him, He bends low to you.</p><p>This is the gentle difference: not a better technique for ending suffering, but a Person who enters into it with you. He calls you not a seeker laboring alone, but a beloved child. And to a heart that has carried the weight of the path by itself, His invitation is simply this: come, and find rest.</p>`}
